title._content: Main Street from head of Central Square of Keene NH, with Soldiers' Monument

description._content: TITLE Main Street from head of Central Square of Keene NH, with Soldiers' Monument, looking south. CREATOR Allen, W.P., Gardner, Mass. SUBJECT Buildings - NH - Keene Town squares Statues Business districts - NH - Keene Stores and shops - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Autoglyph print of Main Street from the head of Central Square looking south down Main Street, in Keene New Hampshire. Taken sometime between the erection of the Soldiers' Monument in 1871 and 1886. The Cheshire House appears on the left and the Unitarian Church, with its tall steeple, a little farther down Main Street. PUBLISHER Keene Public Library DATE DIGITAL 20080201 DATE ORIGINAL 1871? - 1886? RESOURCE TYPE photographs FORMAT image/jpg RESOURCE IDENTIFIER hsykcsq033 RIGHTS MANAGMENT No known restriction on publication.
